@node "Introduction" "Introduction"

                                 @{b}Introduction@{ub}
                               @{fg fill}Ż ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ Ż@{fg text}

DComment is (guess ;)) a Comment Door for @{"FAME" link "FAME" 0}. Its around 100% configurable
(configuration door, textfiles, different sysops for different confs etc).
DComment v1.10p is a major rewrite of the old v1.00p version. Everything has
been enhanced and/or changed. The main enhancement is the flexible handling
of the your sysops. Maybe you noticed a designcrash on users side (DC 1.0)
if sysop specified 10 cosysops and installed big header/tail designs (lets
say 20 lines) but user only defined 25 userlines. Such things are past now.
DComment got a kind of scrolling implemented, try it out, should work fine
:).

DComment has been developed using SAS/C 6.57 on a2000/030/26 (OS3.1).

By the way special thanx to Siegel and Exon for BETATESTING (I mean TESTING,
not just installing as some others did) DCOmment. Actually I'm trying to
create a Support-WWW page with option to download latest betaversions of my
doors. If you are interested or if you just have some
bugreports/suggestions, then @{"contact" link "Contact" 0} me please.

Ah well ... I hope I dont have to explain in detail how to use a Comment,
the user side is quite easy:

- cursor key UP and DOWN to choose the sysop - RETURN to write a comment
  to wished sysop

- SPACE (the long key on your keyboard) to choose
  default sysop (usually the first available sysop)

- direct number input from 1 - 99 + RETURN) for direct choice of a
  special sysop

- c <sysopnumber> : (e.g. C 1) to write a comment to a sysop without
  using the cursor menu


The sysop side is abit more difficult, just read the configuration part and
have a look at the screenshots.


Zod / tRSi (FAME Innovation) '97
@endnode

@node "Configuration" "Configuration"

                                 @{b}Configuartion@{ub}
                               @{fg fill}Ż ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ Ż@{fg text}

There are 2 configuration possibilities:

- the Configuration Door

- Header/Middle/Tail designfiles


                                @{i}@{fg shine}The Config Door@{ui}@{fg text}

First we have the configuration door ... make sure that only your cosys or
only you have access to the door! I guess you have added the door to the
FAME Door config menu(the installer should do that for you), nevertheless,
press "w 14" and choose then "DComment Config".


--[ cut ] -----------------------------------------------------------------

 DCommentCfg v1.01ß (7.3.97) by ZoD!/tRSI (/F-iNNOvATION)

 Sysop: [  1] zOD!
                           1       1o        2o        3o        4o
                          (÷-······-÷-·······-÷-·······-÷-·······-÷-·······
[1] Sysop Name  ........ : ZoD!/lSD^tRSi                                  .
[2] Sysop Name INV ..... : ZoD!/lSD^tRSi                                  .
[3] Sysop REAL UserName  : zOD!                                           .
[4] Sysop Comment ...... : eX-SKYNET sYSOP                                .
[5] Sysop Comment INV .. : rEAD bOOK oF mOD fOR mORE iNFO                 .
[6] Forward Msg's to ... : 0                [        -* NO FORWARD *-     ]
[7] Received Msg's ..... : 78                                             .
[8] Access'o'Meter ..... :[XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX]
                          [XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX]
                                                                          .
(A)dd Entry, (D)elete Entry, (S)ave, (Q)uit:                              .
Cursor Left/Right=Prev/Next, Entrys=[   27]                               .
                                                                          .
--[ cut ] -----------------------------------------------------------------



[1] Sysop Name  ........ : here you insert the current sysops name, you
                           dont have to use the same name as in user.data,
                           furthermore you can use ansi sequences here,
                           just use a '%' instead if the '27' (escape)

[2] Sysop Name INV ..... : here you insert the INVERSE sysop name, that
                           string will appear when you select the sysop
                           with cursorkeys (see screenshots), ansi
                           sequences are of course possible too

[3] Sysop REAL UserName  : here you have to enter sysops real username (as
                           in User.Data), if you dont remember the real
                           username, use a wildcard (eg. zo*), door will
                           help you searching ... :)

[4] Sysop Comment ...... : same options as "Sysop Name" and "Sysop Name INV"
[5] Sysop Comment INV .. : exept that you need to enter a comment for
                           current sysop

[6] Forward Msg's to ... : maybe current sysop is in holidays or whatever,
                           here you can select to whom all messages sent
                           to current sysop will be forwarded (enter the
                           sysopnumber here, on the right side you can see
                           the sysop name then)

[7] Received Msg's ..... : this is just a "how many messages received"
                           counter, you can change it, but do you really
                           want to cheat? :)

[8] Access'o'Meter ..... : this is more or less the bonus track, here you
                           specify if current sysop is available from
                           different conferences, some examples:

                          [XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX]
                          [XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX]

                           here sysop can be selected from EVERY conference

                          [XXX   XXX                                      ]
                          [                                               ]

                           sysop is only availabe from confs 1-3 and 7-9


                           hope its clear what i wanna tell you ;) put a
                           'X' to make sysop availabe or a ' ' to make him
                           'hidden' or however you wanna call it

(A)dd Entry ............ : Add a sysop entry to the end of sysoplist

(D)elete Entry ......... : Delete current entry

(S)ave ................. : Save config

(Q)uit ................. : Quit that nightmare

Cursor Left/Right ...... : select Next / Previous sysop




                        @{i}@{fg shine}The Header/Middle/Tail files@{ui}@{fg text}


First some words about the keyword's format:


                                 %---[KEYWORD]
                                 |||||       |
     introduces the keyword -----'`||`-------^--------------- the keyword
                                   ||
   the length of the string -------'|        L = left formatted
   alway use 2 digits (20,09 ..)    `------- R = right formatted
                                             C = centered
                                             - = no format (pure string,
                                                 no length restriction)

DComment Keywords ARE NOT casesensitiv!





DComment.header ........ : this is just the header design file, DComment
                           provides no keywords for it (no need i think)

DComment.mainline ...... : this is the DComment Mainline design file, it
                           consists of 2 (only two!) lines, the normal
                           mainline and the inverse mainline

--[ cut ] -----------------------------------------------------------------

| [%04RSysopNumber]| %23LSysopname |[%05RMsgsReceived]| %33lsysopcomment |
|>[%04RSysopNumber]| %23LSysopname<|[%05RRATING]| %33lsysopcomment |

--[ cut ] -----------------------------------------------------------------

                           As you can see, the comment design completely
                           depends on you, there is nothing fixed. You can
                           use the following keywords for mainline.dsg:

                           %---SYSOPNAME ..... Sysopname (on INVERSE line
                                               of course INVERSE Sysopname)
                           %---SYSOPCOMMENT .. Sysopcomment or INV Comment
                           %---SYSOPREALNAME . Sysop realname
                           %---SYSOPNUMBER ... Sysop number
                           %---MSGSRECEIVED .. Messagecounter
                           %---RATING ........ still not 1oo%, actually
                                               RATING provides a max 5
                                               digits rating string with
                                               "*" as entrys

DComment.tail .......... : the tailfile is (as header) a normal text file,
                           following keywords are possible:

                           %--TIME ........... shows fame standart
                                               time/date string
                           %--CONF ........... shows current conference
                                               name
                           %--DOORVER ........ shows some (c) info etc :),
                                               if you dont use the keyword
                                               in your design or if its too
                                               short, the string will be
                                               added to the end of tailfile
                                               ( ahh nasty :)) )

                           %B ................ this is NO normal keyword,
                                               it reflects the position of
                                               the small cursor box for
                                               sysopnumber

                           if you wish more keywords, just inform me about,
                           its no prob to add 100 more keywords, but, i did
                           not see any reason for it yet :)


I hope I did not miss anything important. And please forgive me my bad
english:).
@endnode

