@node "History" "History"

                                @{b}DCOMMENT-HISTORY@{ub}
                              @{fg fill}Ż ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ Ż@{fg text}
  31.03.1997  - DComment v1.10p

  + you can choose sysop now via Arguments too, example: c 1 would try to
    write a message to sysop number 1 in current conference
  + recompiled with SAS/C 6.57 (yeah finally i got it installed:))
  - fixed a smart design bug (only appeared when using NComm or a similar
    terminalprogram)
  + no more bugs found so far -> *2.PUBLIC RELEASE*

  08.03.1997  - DComment v1.02

  - fixed a smart but efficient bug in access routines ( if second sysop
    did not have access to current conf, all following sysops became
    "empty" lines )
  - fixed bug with keyword "SYSOPNUMBER" (wasnt correctly counted)
  + added direct keyinput for sysopnumber (up to 99, if you need more,
    send me a EMAIL :))
  - fixed a bug in messagecounting routine, if you had two or more sysops
    with same same, all got a message added (really a bug? or a feature?,
    dunno .. )
  - fixed a major phat bug with cursorbox in tailfile ... first the
    scan for the box wasnt correct (no check for the 'B') and second
    there was a problem when no box available

  07.03.1997  - DComment v1.01

  + recode in SAS/C
  + you can view now 100 sysops on a 25 lines screen WITHOUT any
    design crashes (sorta "scrolling" or "paging" added)
  + 1oo% cfg'able header and tailfiles (keywords DStats like)

    Tailfile keywords are so far:

    %B                  (location of the small cursor box for sysopnumber)
    %--TIME
    %--CONF
    %--DOORVER          (if you dont use DOORVER in your design or
                         if chars < strlen(real DoorVerString),
                         DoorVersion String will added to the end of
                         tailfile )

  + inverse function added (view screenshots ... :))
  - bug in String-Format function found and maybe fixed
  + conference depending sysop-comment added (if sysop dont has the
    smart 'X' for current conf in "Access'o'meter", user wont be able
    to choose him/her for a comment) ( suggestion by Siegel/Trsi )
  + configurable mainlines added, one "normal" mainline and one "inverse"
    mainline, keywordformat is DTools like, first line in
    "DComment.mainline" is "normal" line the second is the "inverse" one

    %---SYSOPNAME
    %---SYSOPCOMMENT
    %---SYSOPREALNAME
    %---SYSOPNUMBER
    %---MSGSRECEIVED
    %---RATING          ( still not 1oo%, actually RATING provides a max
                         5 digit long rating string with "*" as entrys )

  + SPACE == first sysop selected

  xx.11.1996  - DComment v1.00p

  + major rewrite (AMIGA E)
  + lotsa small bugs fixed, code optimized etc
  + you can choose sysops now via number-keys too
  + space = default sysop (sysop #1)
  + messagestatistics included
  - fixed a small enforcerhit
  + *FIRST PUBLIC RELEASE*

  07.09.1996  - DComment v0.20ß

  + configurable "header.txt","middle.txt","tail.txt",
    means they dont need to have a fixed size or whatever
  + tail.txt may contain KEYWORDS, as they are:

    - °S      : here the SysopSelect box will be written
              : (the box with the current sysop number)
    - °TIME   : prints out a time/date string(24 chars)
    - °CONF   : prints out the current conf name(24 chars)

  + you dont need to have any of the 3 text files, but why use
    a comment without design?:)
  - fixed a bug when middle.txt is missing
  + 2 kinds of "cursor" support are avail now
  - fukking bug in output routine fixed (CR/LF stuff),
    reported by marodeur


  xx.08.1996  - DComment v0.10ß

  + first beta (AMIGA E)


                             @{b}DCOMMENTCFG-HISTORY@{ub}
                           @{fg fill}Ż ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ Ż@{fg text}

  31.03.1997  - DCommentCfg v0.21p

  + recompiled with SAS/C 6.57
  - a design bug (like in DComment-Main) fixed
  - another design bug fixed (reported by Exon)
  + *2.PUBLIC RELEASE*

  09.03.1997  - DCommentCfg v0.20ß

  + complete change of cfg file
  + inverse line support / access support etc added
  + sysop names will be checked for existence
  + wildcard search of sysops possible
  + added inverse SysopName
  + ansi support added for:

    Sysop Name
    Sysop Name INV
    Sysop Comment
    Sysop Comment INV

    all normal ANSI sequences should be possible, instead of the
    escape char, just need to enter a "%"

  + recode in SAS/C

  22.10.1997  - DCommentCfg v0.10ß

  + bug in forward/msg's received output fixed
  + yes/no in "special sysop" menupoint selection changed
  + first internal release
@endnode

